questions.quote: Oh, it's good news. No, it's definitely good news. Hold on a second, I have another call. Hey, how's it going?
No wait! Look, wait! Okay, you can hang up, but I'm gonna keep calling! I'm gonna, I'm gonna call everyone in England if that's what it takes to get you to talk to me!
Oh you're not. You're not gonna get in the middle of anything, don't worry about Ross really, really. Oh! Hide! That's Ross! Hide! Hide!
Now we just have to wait for a call and... and someone tells us there's a baby waiting for us. Oh...
Look, this is my home and I want to be able to come and go whenever I want!
I see, but once you get your first paycheck you'll be springing a big hotel suite, right? I mean, lead in a movie, they must be paying you a lot?
So it seemed that my prom date had stood me up, so Ross selflessly, offered to take me.
Yeah! Yeah, it's gonna be a small ceremony. Just family. His.
Yeah, he's the handy man. He's gonna be retiring next week and everyone who lives here is kicking in a 100 bucks as a thank you for all the hard work type of thing.
Listen, can you do me a favor? I'm gonna be out today. Can you just keep an eye on Joey, make sure nothing happens between him and Molly?
